{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This entry describes the head-tail adaptor protein of bacteriophage SPP1\nand related proteins in other bacteriophage and prophage regions of bacterial genomes. Homologues are also found in Gene Transfer Agents (GTA) [[cite:PUB00055430]], including ORFg7 (RCAP_rcc01689) of the GTA of  Rhodobacter capsulatus (Rhodopseudomonas capsulata) [[cite:PUB00055431]].</p>\n\n<p>In bacteriophage SPP1, the gp16 protein functions as a stopper, locking the viral DNA into the capsid. When the tail attachment binds to the entry receptor, gp16 opens by a diaphragm-like motion, allowing the genome to exit the capsid through the tail tube to the host cell. During virion assembly, gp16 functions as a docking platform to which the preassembled tail binds [[cite:PUB00082571]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false} {"text" "<p>The SPP1 head-to-tail connector is composed of cyclical dodecamers of the portal protein gp6 and of the 2 head completion proteins gp15 and gp16 [[cite:PUB00048313]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR038666", "name" "Bacteriophage SPP1, head-tail adaptor superfamily", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"ncbifam" {"TIGR01563" "phage head closure protein"}, "pfam" {"PF05521" "Phage head-tail joining protein"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Bacteriophage SPP1, head-tail adaptor", "short" "Phage_SPP1_head-tail_adaptor"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 11, "domain_architectures" 14, "proteomes" 2383, "taxa" 10314, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 11459, "sets" 0, "proteins" 11454, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 7267}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {"gp" {"displayName" "Genome Properties", "description" "Genome properties is an annotation system whereby functional attributes can be assigned to a gen